cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD

Reasoning: 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper involves analyzing text data from recipes, which falls under the scope of natural language processing. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The study of culinary habits and cuisines around the world involves analyzing social and cultural networks, as well as information sharing on the web. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper involves analyzing a large-scale database of recipes, which requires information retrieval techniques. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The study of health indicators and their relation to culinary habits and cuisines falls under the scope of computers and society. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): While not the main focus of the paper, the analysis of a large-scale database of recipes and health statistics requires software engineering skills and techniques.
